The photocatalytic H2 evolution assessment was performed in a closed 50 mL reactor by a 24 W LED-SMD lamp. For this purpose, in 10 ml of deionized water, 20 mg of AgPdNPs/SLCN catalyst was dispersed by sonication and the reactor oxygen was purged by N2 before the reaction. Then 0.38 ml of 98% FA was injected into the catalyst solution at room temperature. The gas molecules produced were analyzed by a gas chromatograph. The amount of gas (H2 + CO2) evolution during the photocatalytic reaction was evaluated by a gas burette system. The TOFs are calculated within the initial 10 min conforming to the subsequent Eq. 32:TOF=ngasproduced/(nAgPd×h)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
